The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, January 11, 2004  Corporate Briefs																								 Truck and bus maker Ashok Leylands sales surged 36.5 per cent in December following higher demand in domestic and overseas markets. The sales rose to 4,294 units from 3,145 units in December 2002, a company statement said. Domestic sales jumped 31 per cent to 3,847 units, while exports soared 117 per cent to 447 units in the reporting month.																								 US-based BMC Software will acquire the assets of Magic Solutions, a provider of help desk and related software, from Network Associates in a $47-million all-cash deal. The acquisition would also result in BMC Solutions acquiring Magic Solutions research and development operations in Bangalore.																								 Zenith Computers is expecting to cross one lakh PC sales in the current fiscal. We hope to touch Rs 300 crore revenue in the current fiscal, which is about 40 per cent growth from our current revenue of Rs 225 crore, company chairman-cum-managing director Raj Saraf said.																								 Siemens Ltds transportation systems division has bagged a Rs 483 crore order from the ministry of railways for supplying complete electrical systems for Mumbais suburban rail network.																								 BenQ, a leading mobile phone maker in Taiwan, has launched its mobile phones in Calcutta. With its GSM and CDMA handsets, the company plans to capture 5 per cent of the domestic market by 2004.																								 Larsen amp; Toubro (L amp;T), along with its subsidiary Narmada Cement Company, have despatched 1.45 million tonnes of cement and clinker in December 2003 against 1.22 million tonnes in the year-ago period, registering an increase of 19 per cent.																								 Panacea Biotec, a domestic healthcare company, has made a foray into the over-the-counter segment through its best on health products catering to herbal and dietary supplements. 																								 The Aurangabad facility of Orchid Chemicals and Pharmaceuticals has been awarded the ISO 14001 (environment management system) and OHSAS 18001 (occupational health and safety management system) certifications by KPMG.																								 Surya Roshni, a lighting products manufacturer, has received the national award for excellence in energy management from the CII.																								 Icra has assigned a CR3 grading to Rudranee Construction Company, indicating a moderate contract execution capacity.																								 Mahindra amp; Mahindra has been conferred the national energy conservation award for 2003 by the ministry of power. ADVERTISEMENT
